<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-04-02T00:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-04-02T00:36:00-05:00" n="1021" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1021">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.918/20.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-01T23:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 1, 1912—11 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your March 29, 7 p.m. A censor is sitting in the Associated Press office
                            to-night, and it is not yet determined whether a report will be sent or
                            the office closed. Mexican Government will not permit any agency to
                            distribute news harmful to it, whether true or not. As the Government
                            complains of things I know to be true and alleges reports which have
                            never been made, I judge its course neither consistent nor just.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>